Makefile and compile test function

1.	run 'make' first
2.	uncomment main function in the test function 	ex: ft_strtrim.c
3.	gcc ft_strtrim.c -L. -lft
		where	-L.	means look
				-lft		can be expanded to	lib libft.a
						l	is short for lib, therefore it is apparently shortened, and it apparently knows .a extension

